Commentary Text: Arshdeep Singh to Pooran, out Lbw!! They went for a caught behind review, but have got their man LBW. Full and angling in, Pooran moved too far across the line and tried to scoop, missed. Massive deflection and taken well by Jitesh. Seemed like an edge real-time, but if the ump gave not out originally because he felt there was no bat, then wonder why it wasn't given LBW. Plumb in front. Anyway, great innings from Pooran and that RCB record of 263 seems to be safe now. Pooran lbw b Arshdeep Singh 45(19) [4s-7 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Rabada to Mayers, out Caught by Dhawan!! KG wins the battle. That is the 8th wicket for Rabada vs LSG in his 3rd game. What a smart ball. Okay, I know you are smashing anything in the slot, so let me try and cramp you for room and bowl back of a length. This jumped a bit on the batter, Mayers plays an oopsy, this is climbing on me and I have no room to work with too. Wanted to hit down the ground, but the ball hit him high on the bat and balloons to Dhawan. End of a fantastic innings from Mayers. Mayers c Dhawan b Rabada 54(24) [4s-7 6s-4]

Commentary Text: Ravi Bishnoi to Atharva Taide, out Caught&Bowled!! The ball went straight up. The bowler went back a few paces, had eyes on the ball and took it close to his chest. The bowler fell on his back as he lost his footing but managed to hang on to it. That was a tossed up googly, the batter went for the slog sweep and managed to sky it. The ball went high but the bowler always had it covered. Huge strike for LSG as Atharva Taide was the set batter. Atharva Taide c and b Ravi Bishnoi 66(36) [4s-8 6s-2]

Commentary Text: Stoinis to Atharva Taide, SIX, Taide advances, gets a short ball and still manages to whack it for six! He was hitting towards the long boundary at deep backward square, and there was a fielder present at the boundary as well. But he clears him.
